headline: BNY Mellon signs multiyear deal with OpenAI, WSJ reports
summary: Bank of New York Mellon announced a multiyear relationship with OpenAI that will see the bank gain access to cutting-edge OpenAI tools such as Deep Research and its most advanced reasoning models to be combined with the bank’s internal AI platform, Eliza, The Wall Street Journal’s Isabelle Bousquette reported. In return, OpenAI said it hopes to gain insight into how well its models work for complex tasks in the real world, adds the Journal, which notes that terms of the deal weren’t disclosed. “
